---
import Layout from '~/layouts/MarkdownLayout.astro';
const metadata = { title: 'Privacy Policy | Launch.Skin' };
---
<Layout frontmatter={metadata}>
<p><em>Last Updated: March 2026</em></p>

<h2>1. Introduction</h2>
<p>Launch.Skin ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting the privacy of skin practitioners and clinic owners. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard the information related to your boutique website and clinical portfolio services.</p>

<h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
<p>To provide our services, we collect the following types of information:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Clinic Identity:</strong> Business name, practitioner name, professional bio, and contact information.</li>
    <li><strong>Social Media Content (Insta-Sync™):</strong> With your permission, we access public Instagram media, captions, and timestamps to automatically update your website gallery.</li>
    <li><strong>Review Data:</strong> Publicly available Google Business Profile reviews used to populate your clinical "wall of love."</li>
    <li><strong>Technical Data:</strong> Analytics regarding website performance, though we prioritize privacy-first tracking that avoids invasive cookie usage.</li>
</ul>

<h2>3. How We Use Your Data</h2>
<p>We use the collected data solely to:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Build and maintain your dedicated clinical website at your vanity URL (launch.skin/yourclinic).</li>
    <li>Facilitate real-time portfolio updates via our Instagram sync technology.</li>
    <li>Operate the QR-based review engine to help grow your practice's reputation.</li>
    <li>Process payments via secure third-party processors (PayPal). We do not store credit card information on our servers.</li>
</ul>

<h2>4. Data Sharing and Third Parties</h2>
<p>We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal or business data. We share data only with the following essential services:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Hosting Providers:</strong> To keep your clinical site live 24/7.</li>
    <li><strong>Sync APIs:</strong> Communication with Instagram/Meta and Google for portfolio and review functionality.</li>
    <li><strong>Legal Requirement:</strong> If required by law in the State of Delaware or federal US authorities.</li>
</ul>

<h2>5. Security</h2>
<p>We implement industry-standard security protocols to protect your clinic's digital presence. Our "Zero Maintenance" architecture reduces traditional CMS vulnerabilities, keeping your data and your patients' trust secure.</p>

<h2>6. Contact Us</h2>
<p>For questions regarding your data, contact our support team via the contact page.</p>
</Layout>
